        <abstract> 
<p>Sends his paper ["Die selbst-sterilität des Roggens", <hi rend="italic">Landwirtsch. Jahrb.</hi> 6 (1877): 1073–6] on self-sterility in <hi rend="italic">Secale cereale</hi>. AWR was wrong in claiming <hi rend="italic">Beta vulgaris</hi> was perfectly self-sterile.</p> 
            <p>Reports results of crossing wheat varieties. In the first generation offspring are always uniform; some are intermediate, some resemble one parent. In the second generation, on the contrary, he got a diversity of parental and intermediate forms.</p>
        </abstract>
